text: S. S. Chandran (Tamil: எஸ். எஸ். சந்திரன்; died October 9, 2010) was a comedy actor, producer and politician from Tamil Nadu, India. He belonged to the All India Anna Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam party and was a Member of the Parliament representing Tamil Nadu in the Rajya Sabha, the upper house of the Indian Parliament.

Maulana Abdur Rahman was member of the 2nd Lok Sabha. He represented the Jammu constituency of Jammu & Kashmir and was a member of the Congress (I) political party. He was in office from April 1957 to March 1962.
